1. Library Management System

Features:

• Manage books (add, update, delete, search).
• Track borrowers and their borrowing history.
• Allow users to borrow and return books.

Rules:

• A book can only be borrowed if it is available.
• A member can borrow a maximum of 5 books at a time.
• Borrowed books must be returned within 15 days.

Classes:

• Book: Represents book details like title, author, ISBN, and availability.
• Member: Represents a library member with attributes like name, ID, and borrowing 
history.
• Library: Handles operations like adding/removing books, searching, and managing 
borrow/return actions.